description: A TV studio finds its halls terrorized by a phantom just as the Scooby Gang is set to appear as guests to discuss their mystery busting adventures! Could the ghoul be a former host? Find out in "The Phantom of the Opal"!

description: Join Buffy novelist and Bram Stoker Award-winner Nancy Holder as she uncovers the sexy noir thriller secrets of 'The Catalina Caper.' Hollywood has come to the island, and the Domino Lady's alter ego will make her big screen debut. But, there is a matter of blackmail under the lights to attend to!

description: Don Bluth's Space Ace continues the adventures of the musclebound hero Ace! It is up to Dexter - Ace's younger incarnation - to rescue Kimberly and prevent Borf using the Infanto Ray to conquer Earth!

The villainous Commander Borf has attacked Ace with the 'Infanto Ray,' a weapon that transforms him into an adolescent version of himself, and kidnapped his girlfriend Kimberly. 
 
It is up to Dexter, Ace's younger incarnation, to rescue Kimberly and prevent Borf from using the Infanto Ray to conquer Earth!

description:
It's Batman, Robin and Abuse against Zsasz's army! Will the heroes be able to save the captured children in time? 
  
And in the Manhunter co-feature, the trial takes a turn as Jane Doe has a new suspect on her rader - the ever dangerous Black Mask!
 
(note: DC managed to mess up their preview for this Streets of Gotham (as well as the previous one), as the content itself has nothing to do with what is described (no Zsasz, Black Mask, Robin etc.)

description: For some reason, starting with his issue the apperence of many of the characters change for no reason, with Birdman suddenly changing from flying via a costume to having wings coming out of his back, and Blast Bennett's hair going from brown to red.
Last Fox superhero Thor, in the next issue he would be replaced by Dynamite Thor, a different charater with no superpowers.

"Out For Blood" SPIDEY needs a favor from the BLACK CAT. Nothing big. he just needs her help stealing one of MR. NEGATIVE'S most valuable posessions. It's not like anything could go oh-so-horribly wrong! Also in this ish: a dark turn for CARLIE COOPER, a disturbing development for CURT CONNERS, and a malicious move by...AUNT MAY?!
name: Out For Blood

description: Natasha Romanoff's search for the truth behind the Icepick Protocols has taken her around the globe - and now she rockets straight into outer space! It's over the top action all the way - featuring the other Black Widow and two Captain America's - as Marvel's deadliest beauty finally uncovers which part of her past has come to bite her!
name: Chapter Four

description: SIEGE BLOCKBUSTER TIE-IN!! The secrets of the Sentry are revealed but is it too late? Is this a hero reborn or a eulogy? The most pivitol moment in this controversial character's life yet is here, and how it affects the siege on Asgard will leave you breathless.
name: The Void Rising

description: Look! Up in the sky! It's a bird...it's eating brains...it's the VULTURE! While a brand new Vulture terrorizes Spider-Man and New York City in the pages of Amazing, the original Vulture, Adrian Toomes, reflects on his past as Fred Van Lente and Barry Kitson bring you the Vulture's origins. Then, BEN REILY! You asked for him, and J.M. Dematteis and Chad Hardin got 'im. During his years on the road, Ben finds himself in Oregon...and up against a desperate man. Finally, in THE SPECTACULAR SPIDER-GIRL, a gang war heats up...and May doesn't know who to trust when the BLACK TARANTULA strikes!
name: Gauntlet Origins: Vulture, The Spectacular Spider-Girl: Choosing Sides, Ben Reily: Nobody

description: Donatello confronts the mysterious new robot. Why is it motivated to assimilate hosts and what is its relationship to the Baxter Stockman Robot? Don is overwhelmed by the many unknown questions he must answer in order to defeat this major new menace.

The most notable thing about this comic is the ad on the cover and inside front page (see images for Fox) for Kooba Cola, “The Big Drink.”

There was no such thing as Kooba Cola, Victor Fox’s idea (scheme) was that all the kids seeing the ads for Kooba in all his comics (and he was known to claim to be the king of comics) they would demanded to be able to try it, and so Fox could then sell the rights to the name to a bottler. 
 
It didn't work.

description: Scrooge, Donald, and the nephews are back from their hunt for the Number One Dime and are ready to embark on a brand new treasure hunt! Strap in for fun as we take you on another classic adventure from Duckburg to the furthest reaches of the globe courtesy of BOOM Kids!
name: Around the World in 80 Bucks

description: Shadowed by an unseen pursuer, Jack seeks work at the Oatley Tap, a run-down bar populated by dead-enders and drunken cowboys. There he must face a mysterious stranger whose cold dead eyes conceal his darker purpose.

volume.name: The Talisman: The Road of Trials

description: Last April BOOM! Studios showed the world that 'Mark Waid Is Evil' with the smash-hit series Irredeemable. Now BOOM! shows the world that Mark Waid is Incorruptible! The reformed supervillain Max Daring faces up against his oldest ally-in-crime, but this time the fate of a city is at risk! The flip side to Irredeemable, examining the hard, difficult road to changing your ways and making a difference in the world. Covers by Dennis Calero and Rafael Alberquerque.

Their search for Excalibur leads Hunter and company to Italy and the Sword In The Stone. Which isn't Excalibur. The mystery deepens, the clues grow stranger, and there's also punching, kicking and things blowing up! Writers Andrew Cosby and Caleb Monroe keep this careful-what-you-wish-for action-adventure in overdrive with sensational interior art by hot newcomer artist Matt Cossin. Covers by Phil Noto and Ming Doyle.
name: Blood From Stones

description: General Hawk's new operative has found Chuckles... who's in no mood to be rescued. And considering how his last handler ended up, maybe she should take his advice and leave him alone. Meanwhile, delve deeper into Cobra's twisted inner circles as Tomax and Xamot are called before the high command.
name: Scales

description: An all-new ongoing Cars storyline from BOOM! Kids. Lightning McQueen decides to hold a rally race in Radiator Springs, with the proceeds going to charity. Unfortunately, old rivals like Chick Hicks are feeling a little less than charitable!

Manga artist Torajiro Kishi (Maka-Maka) and blockbuster anime studio Madhouse (Trigun, Paprika, Ninja Scroll) love comics. So much so that they've decided to publish an original, Western-style comic exclusively with Dark Horse! Enter Devil, a thrilling, sci-fi take on the vampire genre. A virus is raging across the planet, turning people into bloodsucking superhumans referred to as "Devils." Most victims die within days, sometimes months, but there's a new strain, a new class of Devil that threatens to overtake mankind with power and bloodthirst. This new class of Devils derive from an experiment to clone a virus victim, and it looks like science has created a true monster this time. Can Takimoto and the Devil Investigation Section of the Tokyo police force stop this societal scourge? We'll just have to see.

name: Venezia, la Luna e... il Voyeur! (249 / II)
